mainDV_sterility: In your opinion, how likely is it that the COVID-19 vaccine can cause sterility? (1-7 scale; 1 = Extremely unlikely, 7 = Extremely likely)
DV_Bill.Gates: In your opinion, how likely is it that Bill Gates is connected to the COVID-19 pandemic or its vaccine?  (1-7 scale; 1 = Extremely unlikely, 7 = Extremely likely)
vaccine_willingness: Once made available for you, will you agree to get vaccinated against COVID-19? (1 = Yes, 2 = No, 3 = Maybe, 4 = I got vaccinated already)
distress_COVID: To what extent do you feel distressed about the COVID-19 pandemic? (1 = Not at all, 2 = Slightly, 3 = Moderately, 4 = Considerably, 5 = Significantly)
worried_covid_1: How worried are you that you might contract the virus? (1 = Not worried at all, 2 = Not worried, 3 = Neutral, 4 = Worried, 5 = Very worried, 6 = I have already contracted the virus)
worried_covid_2: How worried are you that your loved ones might contract the virus? (1 = Not worried at all, 2 = Not worried, 3 = Neutral, 4 = Worried, 5 = Very worried, 6 = I have already contracted the virus)
Consecutively: Did you complete the questionnaire consecutively? (1 = Yes, 2 = No)
Disturbances: While completing the questionnaire, did you experience any external disturbances? (1 = No, 2 = If yes, please specify)
alone: Did you fill in this questionnaire alone or with someone else? (1 = Alone, 2 = With someone else)
purpose: What do you think was the purpose of the study?
purpose_specify: When did you think about it, now (when you were asked) or during the study? (1 = Now, 2 = During the study)
stance_vaccine: What was your stance towards the COVID-19 vaccination before participating in this study? (1 = In favor of the vaccine, 2 = Against the vaccine, 3 = Not sure)
familiarity_sterility: Have you ever heard the claim before that the COVID-19 vaccine might cause sterility? (1 = No, 2 = Yes)
familiarity_BillGates: Have you ever heard the claim before that Bill Gates is connected to the COVID-19 vaccine or its vaccine? (1 = No, 2 = Yes)
Attention.check: Which of the following is your favorite sport to watch? This is a data quality check. Regardless of your true preference, please select "Hockey". (1 = Tennis, 2 = Baseball, 3 = Hockey, 4 = Soccer)
marital.status: (1 = Single, 2 = In a serious relationship, 3 = Married, 4 = Divorced, 5 = Separated, 6 = Widowed, 7 = Other)
children: Do you have children? (1 = Yes, 2 = No)
education: What is your highest level of education? (1 = Less than a high school diploma, 2 = High school graduate, 3 = Bachelor's degree, 4 = Master's degree, 5 = Professional degree, 6 = Doctorate)
political.affiliation: (1 = Republican, 2 = Democrat, 3 = Independent, 4 = Prefer not to identify)
Condition: 1 = TF & sci. Correction ; 2 = TF & correction no source; 3 = TF & baseline; 4 = Control & sci. Correction ; 5 = Control & correction no source; 6 = Control & baseline
exclusion: 1 = technical exclusions; 2 = preregistered exclusions; 0 = final sample
Correction: 1 = Correction with sci. Source; 2 = Correction no source; 3 = Baseline (no correction)
